..TEXT:
|che~ = ^in cui.
..TEXT:
|i crin~: "His rays."  See ^Aen.~ IX, 638: "crinitus Apollo"
("long-haired Apollo").
..TEXT:
|tempra~:  This can mean either "cools" or "warms."  See
Statius, ^Silvae~ I, ii, 14-15: "crinem temperat" ("tempers the
tresses").
